external_knowledge:
- Flourished rapidly refers to job growth rates above 10%; 
- Positive growth refers to industry growth rates above 0; 
- Versatile educational background refers to occupations having more than one education level considered.

- 'Growing' job growth trend refers to occupations expected to have an increase in employment opportunities; 
- NAICS (North American Industry Classification System) codes categorize businesses by industry; 
- 'Top 3 occupations' implies the three occupations with the highest projected number of new jobs within each industry.

sql:
SELECT wage_growth_trend, AVG(wage_growth_rate_2020_2025) AS avg_wage_growth_rate
FROM wage_statistics
GROUP BY wage_growth_trend;
